      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey, i'm trying to build this little tool to find flaky tests in our CI pipeline. basically i need a function `detect_flakiness(func, n_runs=10)` that takes a function and runs it $n$ times. if the results are inconsistent, it should return True (it's flaky), otherwise False.\n\nanyway, i've got some tests i need to pass. can u write the function for me?\n\n```python\nimport random\n\ndef test_flaky_function():\n    # This function is flaky, it returns True sometimes and False others\n    return random.choice([True, False])\n\ndef test_stable_failure():\n    # This function always fails/returns False\n    return False\n\ndef test_stable_success():\n    # This function always succeeds/returns True\n    return True\n\n# The tracker should only return True for the flaky one\nassert detect_flakiness(test_flaky_function) == True, \"Should detect flakiness\"\nassert detect_flakiness(test_stable_failure) == False, \"Stable failure is not flaky\"\nassert detect_flakiness(test_stable_success) == False, \"Stable success is not flaky\"\n\nprint(\"All tests passed!\")\n```",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
